This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques. The use of convolutional and deconvolutional layers, as well as skip connections, is a common approach in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of recurrent layers, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The use of level-set methods and optimization techniques may also suggest that this paper could belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of medical imaging datasets and brain tumor segmentation may suggest that this paper could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
